## Key Code

**Plan panel rendering** (`plan-panel.ts` `renderPlanLines()`):
```ts
// Only shows flat labels — no substep detail
for (const s of steps) {
    if (s.errored) rows.push({ icon: "✗", label: s.label });
    else if (s.completed) rows.push({ icon: "✓", label: s.label });
    else if (s.active) rows.push({ icon: frames[idx], label: s.label });
    else rows.push({ icon: "○", label: s.label });
}
```

**PlanStep type** — no detail/substep field:
```ts
interface PlanStep {
    label: string;      // e.g. "✓ Scout: Find vision router extension user"
    completed: boolean;
    active: boolean;
    errored?: boolean;
}
```

**Activity feed already has rich substeps** (`activity-feed.ts`):
```ts
// Substeps track tool-level activity
interface Substep {
    label: string;      // e.g. "Reading path/to/file.ts", "Running: grep -r auth"
    completed: boolean;
    startTime?: number;
    endTime?: number;
}
```

**`toolCallToSubstep()`** already generates descriptive labels:
```ts
case "read":   return `Reading ${normalizePath(input?.path || ...)}`;
case "bash":   return `Running: ${(input?.command || "...").slice(0, 40)}`;
case "grep":   return `Searching: ${input?.pattern || "..."}`;
case "edit":   return `Editing ${normalizePath(input?.path)}`;
case "write":  return `Writing ${normalizePath(input?.path)}`;
```

**`renderCombinedProgress()`** already renders orchestrator steps + subagent substeps — but it's used for chat tool blocks, NOT the plan panel widget:
```ts
// Shows: "→ Scout: investigate auth... [scout]" with substeps indented below
// This rich format is NOT sent to the plan panel widget
lines.push(`→ ${step.label}... [${specialistName}]`);
for (const sub of visibleSubs) {
    lines.push(sub.completed
        ? `  ✓ ${sub.label}`
        : `  ${SPINNER_FRAMES[...]} ${sub.label}...`);
}
```

**Update flow gap** — in `subagent-runner.ts`, `onUpdate` sends feed text to chat history only:
```ts
// This updates the chat tool block, NOT the plan panel widget
const text = orchestratorActivity
    ? renderCombinedProgress(orchestratorActivity, specialist.name, feed, "")
    : renderActivityFeed(specialist.name, feed);
onUpdate?.({ content: [{ type: "text", text }], details: {...} });
```

