### 2. Plan Panel Rendering Edge Cases

#### Empty/undefined detail — **SAFE**
```ts
// updatePlanStepDetail (line ~230)
planState.steps[idx].detail = detail || undefined;

// renderPlanLines (line ~78)
const suffix = r.detail ? ` — ${r.detail}` : "";
```
Empty string converts to `undefined` via `||`. Render uses falsy check. No crash. Clean.

#### Very long detail — **NO TRUNCATION ⚠️**
```ts
const suffix = r.detail ? ` — ${r.detail}` : "";
lines.push(`  ${r.icon} ${r.label}${suffix}`);
```
`goal` is truncated at 55 chars (`goalTrunc`), but **`detail` is not truncated**. Long detail text will push widget past BUDGET (10 lines) or overflow terminal width. The row trimming only limits *row count*, not *row width*.

#### Multiple active steps — **SAFE (only one active at a time)**
The code enforces single-active invariant:
- `pushPlanStep`: marks previous active as completed before pushing new active
- `startDelegationStep`: Case 1 relabels existing active; Case 2 activates first pending; Case 3 appends new
- `findIndex((s) => s.active)` always returns first match

**BUT**: `pushPlanStep` and `startDelegationStep` can race if called in rapid succession before render. Both use `findIndex` on same frame — no explicit lock. In practice, JS is single-threaded so this is safe.

#### Cache invalidation — **SAFE, but misses spinner-only changes sometimes**
```ts
function _renderWidget(): void {
    const lines = renderPlanLines();
    // Line-by-line comparison with _lastWidgetContent
    if (_lastWidgetContent && _lastWidgetContent.length === lines.length) {
        let same = true;
        for (let i = 0; i < lines.length; i++) {
            if (_lastWidgetContent[i] !== lines[i]) { same = false; break; }
        }
        if (same) return;
    }
    _lastWidgetContent = lines;
    _setWidget(WIDGET_KEY, lines);
}
```
